Key Match Events: James McCann hit three home runs
Heston Kjerstad hit a home run
Albert Suarez pitched six smooth innings allowing solo home runs to Carlos Santana and DaShawn Keirsey Jr.
Post-Match Reflections: Brandon Hyde expressed pride in the Orioles' performance
Rocco Baldelli acknowledged the Twins' struggles and the work needed for the offseason
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles finished with 235 home runs, two behind the Yankees for the major league lead
The Orioles will play in a second straight postseason for the first time since 1996-97
The Twins finished with an 82-80 record, losing 27 of their last 39 games
Others: The Orioles will face Kansas City in the first round of the playoffs
Bailey Ober gave up three runs in five innings to finish 0-3 in his final nine starts
Corbin Burnes will pitch Game 1 for the Orioles in the wild card series, with Cole Ragans taking the mound for the Royals
